	<text>
		<body>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Richmond <sic>va.</sic></placeName> <date>March the 8. 5618</date>.</p>
				<p>To the Editor of the Occident Rev. <addressee>Mr. I. Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Rev. Sir&#33;</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">It may not be uninteresting to you to receive<lb/> an account of the progress and <sic>wellfare</sic> of the Congregation<lb/> &#8220;Benesseth Israel&#8221; formed about 18 months ago in this City.<lb/>  The Minhag is the <sic>polish</sic> one&#44; upon the most orthodox princip<lb/>les.  Our progress has been gradual and steady&#44; and I am happy<lb/> to inform you&#44; that we were enabled to consecrate a beautiful<lb/> &#8220;Sephar Tora&#8221; last <date><sic>monday</sic></date>&#44; <add>Hebrew</add>&#44; through the beneficence of<lb/> <persName>Mr. Louis Cohn</persName>&#44; who had it <sic>writen</sic> especially for him in <placeName>Europe</placeName>.<lb/>  <persName>Mr. F. Bendann</persName> officiated in the Camonics<add>&#63;</add> usual upon such<lb/> occasion and the <persName>Rev. Mr Michelbach</persName> of the <sic>german</sic> Cong. delivered<lb/> an appropriate address.  In a short time the Cong. expects<lb/> to be enabled to remove to a more enlarged and convenient<lb/> place of worship&#44; which will no doubt conduce to their<lb/> prosperity and advancement.</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)">Yours respectfully and truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(11)"><persName role="author">F. Bendani</persName></p>
		</body>
